


Image(logo.jpg, thumbnail, left, 350) 211 Yolo is a free telephone information and referral line. Yolo County residents may call the line to find services that can provide help with food, housing, employment, Medical Services health care, counseling, and much more. The number also has a website, http://www.icarol.info/PublicResourceDirectoryFrm.aspx?org2271 www.211yolo.org, containing information about said services.

You may be interested in the Interfaith Rotating Winter Shelter and the CommuniCare Health Center for basic shelter/medical needs.  You can probably recharge your cell phone for a refundable deposit at the Solar Filling Station, depending on which charger shape your phone takes.  This power will allow you to call 211 Yolo and speak to someone who can connect you to additional help.
